post_text:
We're so excited for our inaugural Festival of the Arts happening TONIGHT! We hope you'll join us. The evening will feature student visual and performing arts from each of our six elementary schools.

Enjoy an art walk and take in the talents of our budding artists. Or, tap your toes to the musical stylings of our bands, choirs and small ensemble performances. We look forward to bringing the community together to showcase the talents of our students and celebrate their collaborative efforts.

Wednesday, March 4, 2020
5 pm to 7 pm
Westar Elementary
17777 W. Westar Drive
Goodyear, AZ 85338

post_text: A look inside the classroom: Our Liberty Elementary School District #25 students shown here working on a Three Act Task. A Three Act Task is a whole group mathematics task consisting of three distinct parts: an engaging and perplexing- Act One. An information and solution seeking- Act Two. And a solution discussion and solution revealing- Act Three. Three Act Math Tasks spark students‚Äô curiosity and brings math alive in the classroom. Our faculty are so inspired to see the children engaged in this process! #LESD25 #ComeGrowWithLiberty

post_text:
Each year Liberty Elementary School District #25 participates in the Scripps Spelling Bee. Today we held our annual district level spelling bee which determines who will go on to compete at the Regional Spelling Bee level.
A special congratulations to this year's winner, Mackenzie Lees from Westar Elementary School! Mackenzie will now move on to the regional competition--we wish her lots of luck!

We are so proud of all the participants--your hard work really showed!

Estrella - Elena Carbullido and Lily Heier (Coach, Angela Torres)
Freedom - Esmira Garcia and Bradley Webb (Coach, Erin Brandon)
Las Brisas - Paul Bailey and Bradley Webb (Coach, Malinda Benson)
Liberty - Ellie Hutchinson and Rylee Baer (Coach, Julie Garcia)
Rainbow - Marissa Yocius and Catriona Lineham (Coach, Elizabeth Ashline)
Westar - Mackenzie Lees and Joshua Spardaro (Coches, Judy Adams and Jennifer Vassily)

post_text:
Important notice for Liberty Elementary School.

The pumps on the water tank at Liberty Elementary School are not functioning properly. At this time, the school does not have water. A crew will be working through the night to make repairs. However, the problem may not be resolved in time for school tomorrow morning. We want to alert you that school may be cancelled tomorrow at Liberty Elementary. As soon as the problem is resolved, we will post an update on the school website. Additionally, we will send another e-mail message to all parents no later than 5:30 a.m. to confirm whether or not the school will be open TOMORROW, Monday, October 29th. In the event that school is cancelled, we will also call all parents using the auto-dialer beginning at 6:00 a.m.
